thread.title: Millburn High School girls tennis doubles team reaches state final
thread.title_full: Millburn High School girls tennis doubles team reaches state final

title: Millburn High School girls tennis doubles team reaches state final
text:
Millburn High School girls tennis doubles team reaches state final October 15, 2015 Last updated: Thursday, October 15, 2015, 10:42 AM The Item of Millburn and Short Hills Buy this photo staff photo by jim connelly Millburn High School's Isabella Waung, left, and Sydney Zirlin, shown here conferring Oct. 8 during the state sectional team tournament semifinals, will vie for the state doubles title Saturday, Oct. 17, at Mercer County Park in West Windsor. 
The Millburn High School duo, should they make it 3-0 with a defeat of their rivals Oct. 17 at Mercer County Park in West Windsor, will hold the title of New Jersey State Interscholastic Athletic Association state doubles champions. 
The tournament final, which is scheduled for 10 a.m., pits top seeds Zirlin and Waung against second seeds Loh and Slater. 
Zirlin and Waung survived a three-set match in the quarterfinals and won in straight sets in the semifinals Oct. 11 at Mercer County Park in West Windsor. 
The Miller duo defeated Sarah Apsey and Chloe Decker of Northern Highlands Regional High School 6-1, 4-6, 10-7 to reach the semifinals. 
Zirlin and Waung posted a 7-5, 7-6 (7-4) semifinal triumph over Moorestown High School's Camilla Hoz de Vila and Andrea Giacobbo. 
MILLER NOTES 
Zirlin is appearing in the state final for the second time. 
In 2013, Zirlin and Anya Zakusilo fell to Stephanie Chen Schmidt and Sandy Xie in an all-Millburn High School final. 
Millburn also appeared in the 2007 and 2008 finals. 
Gabrielle Pritsker and Carly Tonelli were the 2007 runners-up. Emily Bary and Melissa Mann won the crown the following year. 
-Jim Connelly
